## Account Resource Monitor Configuration

### Resource Monitor Settings

| Setting | Value |
|---------|-------|
| **Account** | {{ new_account_name | upper }} |
| **Credit Limit** | {{ account_resource_monitor_limit }} credits |
| **Reset Frequency** | {{ account_resource_monitor_reset_frequency }} |
| **Action at 100%** | {{ account_resource_monitor_action }} |

### Threshold Configuration

The resource monitor will be configured with tiered thresholds:

| Threshold | Credits | Action |
|-----------|---------|--------|
| 75% | {{ (account_resource_monitor_limit | int * 0.75) | round | int }} | Notify |
| 90% | {{ (account_resource_monitor_limit | int * 0.90) | round | int }} | Notify |
| 100% | {{ account_resource_monitor_limit }} | {{ account_resource_monitor_action }} |

### How Budgets + Resource Monitors Work Together

| Component | Purpose | Action |
|-----------|---------|--------|
| **Budget** | Visibility & forecasting | Alerts only |
| **Resource Monitor** | Active cost control | Can suspend |

**Example Timeline:**
- Day 15: Budget forecasts overspend → Alert sent (no action)
- Day 20: 75% of resource monitor limit → Notify alert
- Day 25: 100% of resource monitor limit → {{ account_resource_monitor_action }}

This layered approach provides early warning (budget) and a safety net (resource monitor).